Acknowledgments

UX DESIGN INSPIRATION
---------------------

zterm's terminal UX is inspired by the Hermes agent terminal — a separate
project outside the claw-family ecosystem. The Hermes terminal's streaming
REPL, session management patterns, and command-palette ergonomics
influenced zterm's design at the UX layer only.

zterm is a clean-room Rust reimplementation. No code, resources, or assets
are forked, derived, or copied from Hermes or any Hermes-derived project.
Any similarity to Hermes at the code or data-structure level is
independently arrived at.

zterm is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or a component of the Hermes
project.


THIRD-PARTY DEPENDENCIES
------------------------

zterm builds on many open-source Rust crates. Each retains its upstream
license. A complete list is produced at build time from `Cargo.toml`.
Notable dependencies include:

    ratatui             (MIT)                 terminal UI framework
    crossterm           (MIT)                 cross-platform terminal I/O
    tokio               (MIT)                 async runtime
    reqwest             (MIT OR Apache-2.0)   HTTP client
    tokio-tungstenite   (MIT)                 WebSocket client
    rustyline           (MIT)                 line editor
    serde, serde_json   (MIT OR Apache-2.0)   serialization
    clap                (MIT OR Apache-2.0)   CLI argument parsing
    dotenvy             (MIT)                 .env file loader
    tracing             (MIT)                 structured logging
    anyhow              (MIT OR Apache-2.0)   error handling
    chrono              (MIT OR Apache-2.0)   date/time
    uuid                (Apache-2.0 OR MIT)   UUID generation
    regex               (MIT OR Apache-2.0)   regular expressions

Full attributions are preserved in the compiled binary's license metadata
and must accompany any redistribution of this software per the Apache 2.0
NOTICE requirements.


